news.title: Deadline of pending smart city projects in Thiruvananthapuram to be extended till December
news.para: The additional time will be utilised to complete major pending projects, including the renovation of the Palayam Connemara Market, development of Chalai Market and the construction of multi-level car parking (MLCP) facilities.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body receives Rs 100 crore property tax on March 31
news.para: This historic accomplishment also enabled GHMC to cross 2,000 crore in property tax collection for the first time in its history.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body crosses Rs 150 crore property tax target in FY25
news.para: ​​​By Monday, officials succeeded in recovering around Rs 152 crore from all four zones in property tax. The figure will increase when manual recovery by field staff is taken into account.

news.title: Ranchi civic body sets record with Rs 80.64 crore property tax collection
news.para: A significant portion of the tax came from door-to-door visits during which over Rs 41.81 crore was collected from 1,06,019 taxpayers.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body collects record Rs 510 crore property tax in FY 2024-25
news.para: GVMC has been levying property tax based on market price of the property since 2021-22, replacing the earlier method of calculating tax based on the rental value of the property.

news.title: Property tax in Nashik to rise by 2% from April 1
news.para: The property tax will increase by 50% for new industrial properties coming up in the financial year. The city has two industrial estates of the Maharashtra Industrial Development Corporation (MIDC), at Ambad and Satpur.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body collects Rs 58.6 crore property tax in FY25
news.para: Of the total amount received so far, the lion's share (Rs 42 crore) came from commercial establishments. The rest were from residential properties.

news.title: Nashik civic body introduces new assessment system for properties on rent
news.para: Under this new system, a 30% additional tax will be levied on all rental properties. This replaces the current system, which charges a 100% surcharge on residential rentals and a 400% surcharge on commercial rentals.

news.title: Parsvnath Exotica residents write to Haryana CM over illegal construction in Saraswati Kunj
news.para: The 28-acre gated society with 18 towers and approximately 900 flats is divided into two phases. Phase-2, which consists of towers D4, D5, and D6, directly faces Saraswati Kunj.

news.title: Maharashtra government increases Mumbai's ready reckoner rates by 3.4%
news.para: Municipal corporation areas across the state, except Mumbai, will witness an average increase of 5.95%, while municipal councils and nagar panchayats will see a 4.97% hike.

news.title: Pune civic body's property tax department earns Rs 2,360 crore in FY25
news.para: Interestingly, although property tax is traditionally the biggest revenue source for Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC), it is the building permissions department that has earned more revenue in this fiscal gone by — that too for the second year in a row.

news.title: Guwahati civic body extends deadline for property tax defaulters by a day
news.para: GMC additional commissioner Hemanga Nobis said, "Citizens can pay by April 1st, but will have to do so with a penalty. Those who pay by 31st March midnight will not be charged any penalty."

news.title: Mumbai: BMC set to meet Rs 6,200 crore property tax target for FY25
news.para: Officials were confident that by the end of the day, the remaining 3% would be covered. This year's collection has already exceeded last year's ₹4,856 crore, which dipped due to delayed bill issuance.

news.title: Minimum property registration rates in Pune municipal areas up average 4.2%
news.para: Pune district will see an average RR rate hike of 6.8%, lower than the 8.2% increase in 2022-23. The maximum increase was in rural areas at 10.3%. Across the state, the increase is an average of 3.9%, announced the state revenue department.

news.title: Chandigarh administration announces steep hike in property tax
news.para: These new rates will be effective from April 1. The municipal corporation's (MC) revenue from property tax is expected to increase from Rs 45 crore to 90 crore annually. This marks the first increase in property tax since 2020.

news.title: SC deadline ends, more areas in Aravalis fall to construction
news.para: In October last year, the bench of justices AS Oka and Augustine George Masih allowed Haryana govt six more months to demolish all structures built in the Aravalis that are protected under sections 4 and 5 of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA).

news.title: United Spirits sells property in Mumbai for Rs 172 crore
news.para: The transaction, approved by the company's board, was conducted at arm's length and was not a related party deal, it said in a stock exchange filing, adding that buyers Ajaykumar and Manisha Vaghani will bear all applicable taxes and fees.

news.title: China Vanke reports annual loss of $6.8 billion
news.para: Vanke said 2024 was an "exceptionally challenging year" in a filing to the Hong Kong stock exchange and apologised for "distress caused... due to the significant decline in sales, substantial losses and pressure on our liquidity".

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai rises 9.5% to 15,482 units in March: Knight Frank
news.para: The Maharashtra government earned a revenue of nearly Rs 1,600 crore, an all-time high, through registration of properties in March due to high-value transactions.

news.title: Vanke's unit Onewo to buy remaining stake in Shanghai Xiangda for $120 million
news.para: Onewo will gain full ownership of Xiangda by acquiring the remaining 55% stake through its subsidiary, Onewo Business Enterprise Space Technology.
